
[1]bethink

   BETHINK', v.t. pret. and pp.bethought. [be and think.]

   To call to mind; to recall or bring to recollection, reflection, or
   consideration; generally followed by a reciprocal pronoun, with of
   before the subject of thought.

   I have bethought myself of another fault.

            BETHINK', v.i. To have in recollection; to consider.
